      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(ci): autoscrub dependency lockfile-only PR changes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds deterministic autoscrubbing for package lockfile-only PR changes when the PR branch is in the main OpenClaw repository or a fork branch with maintainer edits enabled.\n- Restores only changed package lockfiles from the PR base tree, then creates one narrow cleanup commit: `chore: remove dependency lockfile change`.\n- Uses a short-lived GitHub App token only for the autoscrub branch cleanup commit and commits through GitHub GraphQL `createCommitOnBranch`, so autoscrubbed heads are real PR head updates instead of `GITHUB_TOKEN` ref writes.\n- Leaves unpushable fork PRs, mixed dependency-related changes, and GitHub write failures blocked with deterministic comments that explain the exact manual next step.\n- Skips autoscrub when any changed `package.json` modifies dependency graph fields, or when dependency-related non-lockfile files such as `pnpm-workspace.yaml` or `patches/**` are also changed.\n\n## User-Facing Comments\n\nThis PR adds one success comment and expands the blocked comment:\n\n- `Dependency lockfile changes were removed`: posted after a successful autoscrub commit, listing restored lockfiles, target branch, and cleanup commit SHA.\n- `Dependency graph changes are blocked`: explains whether autoscrub was not attempted for an unpushable branch, skipped because manifest dependency graph fields changed, skipped because non-lockfile dependency files also changed, or attempted but rejected by GitHub.\n\n## Security / Automation Notes\n\n- The workflow keeps using trusted base checkout under `pull_request_target`; it does not check out or execute PR-head code.\n- The default workflow permissions keep `contents: read`; the autoscrub job uses a head-repository-scoped GitHub App token for the deterministic branch cleanup commit while comments and labels remain authored by `github-actions[bot]`.\n- The final required check remains named `dependency-guard` and reruns the trusted script in enforce mode after the optional autoscrub job.\n- Autoscrub is limited to PR heads with a concrete ref and SHA where maintainers can modify the branch: same-repository branches or fork branches with maintainer edits enabled.\n- Fork autoscrub scopes the App token request to the PR head owner/repository, writes through `createCommitOnBranch`, and falls back to the blocked comment if GitHub rejects token creation or the cleanup commit.\n- Dependency graph changes remain blocked unless the current head SHA is explicitly authorized through the existing secops override flow.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node --check scripts/github/dependency-guard.mjs`\n- YAML parse for `.github/workflows/dependency-guard.yml`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- Direct Node assertions for same-repository autoscrub, fork autoscrub denial, maintainer-editable fork autoscrub, lockfile-only eligibility, and mixed lockfile plus `patches/**` / `pnpm-workspace.yaml` denial\n- Configured App-token owner/repository outputs from dependency guard detect mode and trusted marker-comment author assertions\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/dependency-guard-workflow.test.ts test/scripts/dependency-guard-script.test.ts`\n\n",
